The service makes core product system webservices transparent by either executing
old core mainframe webservice
DEPSAccountService
or core renewal webservice
ACCAccountServce
depending on productSystem of input accountNumber.
Available operations: AccountCreateBasic V16_1 AccountReadAggregated V16_1]]> This operation creates a basic deposit account and attaches it to a given customer and product. <br> This includes: <br> create an account <br> relate account to customer <br> Additional information: <br> If AccountNumber is provided, accountNumber acquire will be skipped; Deposit error codes:
2391 - Because of transactions in RTS the account will be terminated in to nights batch (warning)
2100 - Currency deposit not available for update
2101 - Account number not within organization
2102 - Account number generation not available for organization
2103 - Account number reserved
2104 - Account number used
2105 - Profit center not used by organization
2106 - Function not available to organization
2107 - Bank not found
2108 - Account number not in correct bank table account series
2109 - Error reading bank table
2110 - Product does not allow deposit accounts
2111 - Product does not allow creating accounts
2112 - Product id reserved credit line
2113 - Product does not exist
2114 - Profit center id not found
2115 - Currency code does not exist
2116 - Currency code is not found in organization currency rates
2117 - Account number already exist
2118 - Product main group does not exist
2119 - Product sub group does not exist
2120 - Product use group does not exist
2121 - Product needs to be reserved for local currency deposits
2122 - Product use group invalid
2029 - Deviation of total balance limit not allowed for this product (account)
nnnn - Organization Id not in EOM
nnnn - OrgId must be defined
nnnn - Invalid Product type
nnnn - Customer details does not exist
]]> This operation returns details for a deposit account based on the given account number. Deposit error codes:
2000 - Account number not found.
2001 - Account no is not CDV valid.
nnnn - Input Parameter is Incorrect

Available operations: BSUAccountCreate BSUAccountRead
Common error codes: 0 - OK 12 - Data not found for the request. 69 - User not authorized for this operation. 70 - System error. 100 - Resource unavailable. 101 - Environment error. 102 - No response from host system. 200 - Account number can not have a null value 201 - Account number too long. MaxValue is 99999999999L 202 - Account number is too short. MinValue is 1000000000L 1000 - Customer number not found. 1001 - Account number not found. 1003 - Not a valid account number. 1005 - Operation does not handle guarantee accounts. 1006 - Operation does not handle loan accounts. 1007 - Operation does not handle currency deposit accounts. 1008 - ProfitCenter not found within OrgId. 1009 - Security violation; invalid bank number. 1999 - Unknown error from the host system.</documentation> </annotation> <import namespace="urn:corews.enterprise.fs.edb.com:domain:common:v1"/> <import namespace="urn:enterprise.fs.edb.com:domain:common:v1"/> <import namespace="urn:srv.dep.savings.fs.edb.com:domain:bsuaccount:v13_1"/> <element name="bsuAccountCreateRequest" type="tns:bsuAccountCreateRequestType"/> <element name="bsuAccountCreateResponse" type="tns:bsuAccountCreateResponseType"/> <element name="bsuAccountCreateFault" type="enterprisecommon:responseStateCodedFault"/> <element name="bsuAccountReadRequest" type="tns:bsuAccountReadRequestType"/> <element name="bsuAccountReadResponse" type="tns:bsuAccountReadResponseType"/> <element name="bsuAccountReadFault" type="enterprisecommon:responseStateCodedFault"/> <complexType name="bsuAccountCreateRequestType"> <annotation> <documentation>This operation creates BSU savings account and agreement attributes. The account number must be created in the deposit system before creating the BSU attributes. It is possible to create a new BSU (bsuAccountCreateNewBSUType), or transfer an existing BSU (bsuAccountCreateTransferBSUType) from another bank or person.</documentation> </annotation> <sequence> <element name="qualification" type="account:bsuAccountCreateQualificationType"/> <choice> <element name="newBSU" type="account:bsuAccountCreateNewBSUType"/> <element name="transferBSU" type="account:bsuAccountCreateTransferBSUType"/> </choice> </sequence> </complexType> <complexType name="bsuAccountCreateResponseType"> <annotation> <documentation>Returns the response state which says if the operation was a success or not. No other output values are returned. Error codes: 2129 - Account does not exist 2130 - BSU is already registered 2131 - Account is not a savings account 2132 - Account is terminated 2133 - Account is blocked 2134 - Customer number is not valid 2135 - Can not create BSU when person turns 34 this year or already 34 years or older 2136 - Account has wrong account description code 2137 - Deposit this year exceeds maximum 2138 - Available interest must be greater than or equal to interest this year 2139 - Balance must be equal to sum of the other amounts 2140 - Start date in NewBSU must be between 1.january and todays date 2141 - Start date in TransferBSU must be between 01.01.1992 and todays date 2142 - Blocked balance can not be supplied 2143 - Blocked interest can not be supplied 2144 - Savings deduction history can not be supplied 2145 - Interest deduction history can not be supplied 2157 - Invalid reference customer number 2036 - Blocked balance is too long 2037 - Blocked interest is too long 2038 - Savings deduction history is too long 2039 - Interest deduction history is too long 2040 - Interest this year is too long 2041 - Deposit this year is too long 2042 - Available interest is too long 2043 - Balance is too long 2044 - Forced debt relief is too long</documentation> </annotation> <complexContent> <extension base="enterprisecommon:baseResponseType"/> </complexContent> </complexType> <complexType name="bsuAccountReadRequestType"> <annotation> <documentation>This operation returns details for a BSU savings account based on the given account number or customer key. If customer key is given, the operation will retrieve the given customer's BSU savings account and return the details. In case the customer key is given only valid BSU saving account will be returned, whereas in case if account number given account with terminated BSU could be returned.</documentation> </annotation> <sequence> <element name="qualification" type="account:bsuAccountReadQualificationType"/> </sequence> </complexType> <complexType name="bsuAccountReadResponseType"> <annotation> <documentation>Returns BSU savings account details. Error codes: 2154 - Account has no BSU agreement 2156 - No valid BSU agreement exists 2159 - Customerid has to be set 2160 - Invalid date 2161 - Field must be numeric 2163 - A closed BSU agreement was found</documentation> </annotation> <complexContent> <extension base="enterprisecommon:baseResponseType"> <sequence> <element minOccurs="0" name="result" type="account:bsuAccountReadResultType"/> <element minOccurs="0" name="customerInformation" type="corewscommon:customerInformationType"/> </sequence> </extension> </complexContent> </complexType> </schema> <schema
